retry: run a command until it succeeds
Copyright (C) 2020 Jeremy Grosser <jeremy@synack.me>

GPL-2.0 license. See COPYING for details.

Usage
=====

    retry -h -n NUM_RETRIES -b BACKOFF -m MAX_BACKOFF -s RETURN_CODE <command>
        -n number of retries to attempt if the command does not return successfully (default: 10)
        -b initial backoff in seconds. Each subsequent failure will double the backoff interval (default: 1.0)
        -m maximum backoff in seconds. (default: unlimited)
        -s return value indicating success of the command. May be used more than once. (default: 0)
        -h this help

Building
========

    ./bootstrap
    ./configure
    make
    make install
